comments: Exported from VSAC and bulk imported to N3C.
intention: Clinical Focus: Transfusion of Blood or Blood Products.; Data Element Scope: Transfusion of blood or certain blood products that exposes a person to transmission of and infection with bloodborn viruses.; Inclusion Criteria: Procedures related to transfusion, push transfusion or exchange transfusion of blood or blood components in newborn, children and adults. limitations: Exclusion Criteria: Procedure excluded: Transfusion of blood expanders, Apheresis procedure, Transfusion of bone marrow, Cord cell transfusion, Plasma/plasma substitute transfusion, Autologous procedures (e.g. autotransfusion). Procedures related to Blood Bank physician services such as: investigation of transfusion reactions, and authorizations for deviations from blood bank procedures.

comments: Exported from VSAC and bulk imported to N3C.
intention: Clinical Focus: Evidence of a hematopoietic stem cell transplant (HSCT) (i.e., bone marrow transplant) in the patient record.; Data Element Scope: Evidence that a HSCT has been performed on the patient. Since SNOMED CT does not provide disorder codes for HSCT, this VS only consists of "disorder" codes that represent complications of HSCT.; Inclusion Criteria: SNOMED CT disorder codes that represent complications of HSCTs (regardless of the type of bone marrow/stem cell transplant). Active and inactive codes since inactive codes are not always updated in a patient record.
limitations: Exclusion Criteria: Complications from other types of transplants, other types of SNOMED codes (e.g., "finding", "situation"). Chronic and Genital Graft vs. Host Disease.
provenance: Steward: MITRE; OID: 2.16.840.1.113762.1.4.1032.220; Code System(s): SNOMEDCT; Definition Type: Extensional; Definition Version: Latest; Accessed: 2022-03-02 14:16:26

concept_set_name: [VSAC] Immunosuppressant medications for inflammatory bowel disease or rheumatoid arthritis
concept_set_version_title: [VSAC] Immunosuppressant medications for inflammatory bowel disease or rheumatoid arthritis (v1)
comments: Exported from VSAC and bulk imported to N3C.
intention: Clinical Focus: The purpose of this value set is to represent immunosuppressive drugs that, when used to treat certain diseases, may put a woman at greater risk of cervical neoplasia and cancer than the general population, as defined by the article "Guidelines for Cervical Cancer Screening in Immunosuppressed Women Without HIV Infection" (Moscicki et al., 2019).; Data Element Scope: RxNorm codes that represent branded and non-branded immunosuppressive medications used to treat either inflammatory bowel disease or rheumatoid arthritis.; Inclusion Criteria: Includes codes that represent immunosuppressant medications used to treat either inflammatory bowel disease or rheumatoid arthritis.
limitations: Exclusion Criteria: Excludes any immunosuppressant medication that is not cited in the stated reference as treatment of either inflammatory bowel disease or rheumatoid arthritis.
provenance: Steward: MITRE; OID: 2.16.840.1.113762.1.4.1032.258; Code System(s): RXNORM; Definition Type: Extensional; Definition Version: Latest; Accessed: 2022-03-02 14:16:26
